    <h3 style="margin-top:28px;">Progression Model</h3>
    <p>Every 1–2 weeks, choose ONE of the following:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Add 1–2 reps per set</li>
      <li>Increase dumbbell weight slightly</li>
      <li>Slow the tempo by 1 second</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Important:</strong> Progress only one variable at a time. If form breaks down, the weight is too heavy.</p>

    <h3 style="margin-top:20px;">Session Reminders</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Rest at least one day between sessions — recovery is where adaptation happens.</li>
      <li>Warm up with 2–3 minutes of arm circles and gentle shoulder rolls before each session.</li>
      <li>Two sessions per week is enough to see meaningful results. Three is ideal.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="pain-rule">
      <strong>Pain Rule</strong>
      <p style="margin-bottom:8px;">Mild muscular fatigue during a set is normal and expected. Stop and modify if you experience any of the following:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Sharp or stabbing pain</li>
        <li>Pain that increases during the set</li>
        <li>Numbness or tingling down the arm</li>
        <li>Symptoms that remain elevated after the session</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
